    <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_district">District</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_geographic_area">GEOGRAPHIC AREA</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_district">Districts</xref>
 are local administrative units. The only current references to 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_district">Districts</xref>
 are found in 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_metropolitan_district">Metropolitan Districts</xref>
 and 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_non-metropolitan_district">Non-Metropolitan Districts</xref>
 in England, and District Council Areas in Northern Ireland.        </p>
